"title": "7942: ministry, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7942",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>All creatures owe their Creator a ministry of service to him and to humanity. The example and teaching of Jesus Christ illustrate this.</p>\n<h2>All human beings owe a ministry of service to God</h2>\n<h3>The debt owed by the creature to the Creator</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:25\">ROM 1:25</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The service of the nations and their rulers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps148:7-Ps148:11\">PSA 148:7–148:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:17\">JER 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:1-Joel3:2\">JOL 3:1–3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:4\">REV 15:4</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of the service of rulers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra1:1-Ezra1:2\">EZR 1:1–1:2</a> <em>Cyrus of Persia</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:9\">JER 25:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:6\">JER 27:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:10\">JER 43:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:4\">ROM 13:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:6\">ROM 13:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>The ministry of the people of God</h2>\n<h3>In the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:6\">EXO 19:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:6\">ISA 61:6</a></p>\n<h3>In the NT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:6\">REV 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:6\">REV 20:6</a> <em>resurrected martyrs</em></p>\n<h2>The ministry of priests, kings and prophets in the OT</h2>\n<h3>The priests</h3>\n<p>Aaron:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:35\">EXO 28:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:2\">NUM 18:2</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:12\">DEU 17:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:2\">1CH 15:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:22\">JER 33:22</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:63\">EZR 2:63</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:6\">HEB 9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:10\">HEB 13:10</a></p>\n<h3>The rulers</h3>\n<p>David:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:18\">2SA 3:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:70\">PSA 78:70</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:69\">LUK 1:69</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:25\">ACT 4:25</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:23\">HAG 2:23</a> <em>Zerubbabel, governor of Judah</em></p>\n<h3>The prophets</h3>\n<p>Moses:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:7-Num12:8\">NUM 12:7–12:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh12:6\">JOS 12:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:7\">2CO 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:5\">HEB 3:5</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:18\">1SA 2:18</a> <em>the young Samuel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:36\">2KI 9:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:10\">2KI 10:10</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:1\">1CH 25:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa20:3\">ISA 20:3</a> <em>Isaiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1-Isa42:4\">ISA 42:1–42:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:25\">JER 7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:4\">JER 25:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:12\">1PE 1:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:7\">REV 10:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:18\">REV 11:18</a></p>\n<h2>The ministry of those specially set aside by the church</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:10\">1TI 3:10</a> <em>Deacons</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:5\">TIT 1:5</a> <em>Elders</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a> <em>Overseers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ fulfils the OT understanding of ministry</h2>\n<h3>His ministry as servant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:18\">MAT 12:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1\">ISA 42:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13\">ACT 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:26\">ACT 3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:27\">ACT 4:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:30\">ACT 4:30</a></p>\n<h3>His ministry as shepherd, teacher and prophet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:13\">JHN 13:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:22\">ACT 3:22</a></strong></p>\n<h3>His ministry as priest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:20\">HEB 6:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:6\">HEB 8:6</a></p>\n<h3>His ministry as king</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:37\">JHN 18:37</a></strong></p>\n<h2>NT ministry follows the pattern of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>In servanthood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:26-Matt20:28\">MAT 20:26–20:28</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:43-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:43–10:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:26-Luke22:27\">LUK 22:26–22:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:11\">MAT 23:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:43\">MRK 10:43</a></p>\n<h3>In teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:20\">MAT 28:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>In shepherding</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:17\">JHN 21:15–21:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>In priesthood by self-sacrifice and intercession in prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:17\">PHP 2:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1\">1TI 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's servants can expect the same response that he received</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:20\">JHN 15:20</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The ministry of angels</h2>\n<p>Angels are both ministers to God's people and fellow-servants with them:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:7\">HEB 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:14\">HEB 1:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:10\">REV 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:9\">REV 22:9</a></p>",
